comment: Size definitely does not matter. At one of the bases my husband worked at, he's military, they got a domestic violence call. The husband was 6'7 and around high 200s in pounds, his wife was 5'4 and around low 100s in pounds. Everyone that was on the way kept thinking how dare this huge man beat his wife. They show up and see HIM bloody and beat so badly he had to go to the hospital for stitches. She took an iron skillet and beat him with it. Few things to remember: 1) don't just assume the man is beating the woman just because she says its true. My husband was also in am abusive relationship with his ex wife. And 2) size does not and will never matter. And 3) get all the facts before taking the sides. During my husband's divorce and it getting out that "he abused his wife" a lot of people left him. When things came to light that it was her, some people came forward and apologized and he excepted but told them he wanted nothing to do with them. Every type of abuse there is, it can happen to both genders.
